//Reverse a string in Python without using slicing.

//1st approach
str="hello"
rev=""
#using loop
for ch in str:
    rev=ch+rev

print(rev)
Time Complexity: O(n²) because string concatenation creates new strings repeatedly.

//2nd approach
def reverse_string(s):
    chars = list(s)
    left, right = 0, len(chars) - 1
    while left < right:
        chars[left], chars[right] = chars[right], chars[left]
        left += 1
        right -= 1
  return "".join(chars) 
Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)
